<LP>
   LAS VEGAS, Nev. -- United Gaming Inc., a gambling machine
operator, said it received approval from state gambling
authorities to take over the operations of the Plantation
Casino in Sparks, Nev.
   United Gaming purchased the casino for $9.5 million six
months ago, and had been awaiting approval from the Nevada
Gaming Control Board and the Nevada Gaming Commission to
operate it.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   United Gaming also said it has agreed to sell the Trolley
Stop, a downtown Las Vegas slot machine parlor, which is
being constructed. The company will retain a participation in
the Trolley Stop's revenue, it said. It declined to provide
details on the price or to identify the purchaser.
</TEXT>
